              margin-top: 2px !important;">Synagogue arson attack</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-10-2.jpg" alt="Synagogue arson attack" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Australian authorities are <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/09/australia/melbourne-australia-synagogue-attack-investigation-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">investigating</a> last week’s arson attack on the Adass Israel Synagogue in Melbourne as a terrorist incident, marking it as a significant act of antisemitism. A joint counter-terrorism team, including Victoria Police, the Australian Federal Police, and ASIO, handles the investigation. Three suspects are being sought, while the federal government has launched Operation Avalite to address a surge in antisemitic incidents and committed $21 million for increased security at Jewish community sites.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">
          Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese noted this event as the third antisemitic incident that has occurred in Australia in recent months. Antisemitism has <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/1-open-hatred-jews-surges-150233311.html" target="_blank">surged</a> globally, inflamed by the Gaza war, with recent events highlighting its dangerous resurgence. In the U.S., Jewish communities face <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2023/10/31/politics/antisemitism-unstable-world-analysis/index.html" target="_blank">threats</a>, such as Cornell University students fearing for their safety after death threats.</p>
        </mj-text>
